<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-48] AUTH_ID not handled correctly when no auth ids are present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-48</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;AUTH_ID is used (usually done using Ids.CREATOR_ALL_ACL ) to represent the id that was used to authenticate with ZooKeeper. Thus, an exception should be raised if there are no authenticated ids present. Currently, the exception is not being raised.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12398665">ZOOKEEPER-48</key>
            <summary>AUTH_ID not handled correctly when no auth ids are present</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
